WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.022 --> 00:00:02.482
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent<i>...</i>

2
00:00:02.565 --> 00:00:04.567
Joanne Drexel.
I'm part of George's legal team.

3
00:00:04.651 --> 00:00:06.027
Changing lives left and right. huh?

4
00:00:06.110 --> 00:00:08.404
- What?
- You're just not what I expected.

5
00:00:08.488 --> 00:00:09.531
<i>Those letters from Malcolm?</i>

6
00:00:09.614 --> 00:00:12.033
- You've gotten quite a few already.
- Okay. thank you.

7
00:00:12.116 --> 00:00:14.577
You know there's no shame
in a next chapter. Amanda.

8
00:00:14.661 --> 00:00:17.539
Guys like that can't be killed.
They just get promoted.

9
00:00:17.622 --> 00:00:18.623
Antonio!

10
00:00:18.706 --> 00:00:22.502
<i>Adelaide was spotted in Brazil.
We don't know if he's with her.</i>

11
00:00:22.585 --> 00:00:23.711
<i>You are The Commander.</i>

12
00:00:23.795 --> 00:00:25.588
- What's this?
- We'll be in touch.

13
00:00:25.672 --> 00:00:27.548
That was really beautiful.

14
00:00:27.632 --> 00:00:28.967
Oh. thank you. Casey.

15
00:00:29.050 --> 00:00:31.219
Do you want to have dinner tonight?

16
00:00:31.302 --> 00:00:32.303
<i>I'll bring the wine.</i>

17
00:00:32.387 --> 00:00:35.223
You threw a rock through
your estranged wife's window last night.

18
00:00:35.306 --> 00:00:37.892
I got a bad feeling about Dallas.
You need protection.

19
00:00:37.976 --> 00:00:40.436
This is my personal gun.
Hang on to it till you get your own.

20
00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:43.106
- <i>He's in the house!</i>
- Get the gun. Remember what I taught you.

21
00:00:43.189 --> 00:00:45.233
<i>Come back here. you bitch!
I'm gonna kill you.</i>

22
00:00:45.316 --> 00:00:46.317
<i>No!</i>

23
00:00:46.401 --> 00:00:47.610
Casey?

24
00:00:56.494 --> 00:00:57.495
I'll let 'em know.

25
00:00:59.539 --> 00:01:00.540
Mm-hmm.

26
00:01:08.298 --> 00:01:09.716
Okay. just breathe.

27
00:01:13.761 --> 00:01:14.762
There she is.

28
00:01:14.846 --> 00:01:16.472
Come on. baby. breathe.

29
00:01:18.266 --> 00:01:19.809
All right. all right.

30
00:01:21.436 --> 00:01:22.729
Oh. good. you're here.

31
00:01:23.354 --> 00:01:26.024
These are the agents I mentioned.
Will Trent and Faith Mitchell.

32
00:01:26.608 --> 00:01:28.109
This is my friend. Casey Mavery.

33
00:01:29.068 --> 00:01:31.529
I'm sorry. I-I I'm just...

34
00:01:32.697 --> 00:01:34.282
It's okay.

35
00:01:34.907 --> 00:01:36.200
You're okay. sweetie.

36
00:01:36.284 --> 00:01:38.620
It's all right. You're okay. All right?

37
00:01:38.703 --> 00:01:42.832
Ms. Mavery. do you mind if I sit with you
while Amanda catches my partner up?

38
00:01:42.915 --> 00:01:43.916
I'm here.

39
00:01:52.091 --> 00:01:55.845
The. uh. uni outside said
this was a domestic dispute?

40
00:01:55.928 --> 00:02:00.099
Yeah. the body is. uh. Casey's
soon-to-be ex-husband. Dallas Mavery.

41
00:02:00.183 --> 00:02:01.309
He didn't live here.

42
00:02:01.392 --> 00:02:03.936
He broke in last night. attacked her.
and she shot him.

43
00:02:05.355 --> 00:02:07.190
Seems pretty clear cut.

44
00:02:07.273 --> 00:02:09.025
Um... I don't mean
to sound callous.

45
00:02:09.108 --> 00:02:10.651
but why did you call me and Faith?

46
00:02:10.735 --> 00:02:13.363
Casey and I are romantically involved.

47
00:02:14.697 --> 00:02:15.740
Oh.

48
00:02:18.451 --> 00:02:20.286
Feels like there's more
you want to say. Amanda.

49
00:02:22.038 --> 00:02:23.039
It was my gun.

50
00:02:24.540 --> 00:02:25.625
Casey didn't feel safe.

51
00:02:25.708 --> 00:02:27.293
He'd been threatening her.

52
00:02:27.377 --> 00:02:29.587
I loaned her my personal weapon
just in case.

53
00:02:30.296 --> 00:02:31.923
And you know what? I'm glad I did.

54
00:02:32.006 --> 00:02:34.133
Don't touch me. please!

55
00:02:34.217 --> 00:02:36.594
Sorry. ma'am. I just brushed her arm.

56
00:02:36.678 --> 00:02:37.679
Okay. go outside.

57
00:02:37.762 --> 00:02:39.222
Ms. Mavery. it's okay.

58
00:02:39.305 --> 00:02:40.515
Can't breathe.

59
00:02:40.598 --> 00:02:43.434
Casey. breathe. That's right.

60
00:02:45.186 --> 00:02:46.187
That's right.

61
00:02:46.979 --> 00:02:47.980
Breathe.

62
00:02:52.360 --> 00:02:55.822
We have our lives ahead of us.
Why would we throw it away to be cops?

63
00:02:56.406 --> 00:03:00.451
We're homicide detectives with
fulfilling careers. It's important work.

64
00:03:00.535 --> 00:03:01.953
If you want to learn more...

65
00:03:02.036 --> 00:03:04.706
take a water bottle.

66
00:03:04.789 --> 00:03:05.790
Ask for Franklin.

67
00:03:05.873 --> 00:03:09.085
Oh. Community Service Day. I love it.

68
00:03:09.168 --> 00:03:10.837
Man. I love it. Don't you love it?

69
00:03:10.920 --> 00:03:13.381
I know you're married.
and you're about to have a baby.

70
00:03:13.464 --> 00:03:16.175
but in this moment. I'm questioning
if you know what the word love means.

71
00:03:16.259 --> 00:03:18.010
You're homicide detectives. right?

72
00:03:18.094 --> 00:03:20.263
- I-I need you to help me.
- With what?

73
00:03:20.346 --> 00:03:21.931
You-You've got to keep an open mind. okay?

74
00:03:22.014 --> 00:03:24.225
I saw something. but. I didn't...

75
00:03:24.308 --> 00:03:27.478
Not... Not in person. but I just...
I... I-I-I get these...

76
00:03:27.562 --> 00:03:28.729
- Get it out.
- Seriously.

77
00:03:28.813 --> 00:03:30.398
I know where a dead body is.

78
00:03:31.065 --> 00:03:34.110
Okay. Where did you see the body?

79
00:03:34.193 --> 00:03:37.155
That-That's the open-mind part.
I get these visions.

80
00:03:37.238 --> 00:03:39.073
Visions. Is it peyote?

81
00:03:39.157 --> 00:03:41.534
Is that what you're on?
Wait till you graduate to do that stuff.

82
00:03:41.617 --> 00:03:43.953
No. no. no. no!
I-I-I need you to listen to me.

83
00:03:44.036 --> 00:03:47.582
I know her. Her name's Nikki.
Nikki Lane. She's my neighbor.

84
00:03:49.333 --> 00:03:51.210
Where did you find Nikki's body?

85
00:03:51.294 --> 00:03:54.130
I didn't. That's what I'm trying
to tell you. okay?

86
00:03:54.213 --> 00:03:56.382
I-I-I see images in my mind.

87
00:03:56.466 --> 00:03:59.886
It's not a complete picture.
but there's a...

88
00:04:01.095 --> 00:04:04.557
a green circle and seven flags.

89
00:04:04.640 --> 00:04:05.641
Oh. like the theme park?

90
00:04:05.725 --> 00:04:09.061
That's Six Flags. Okay. seven flags.

91
00:04:09.145 --> 00:04:11.272
Seven flags. right.
Did you get the green circle?

92
00:04:11.355 --> 00:04:13.149
- I did.
- Okay.

93
00:04:13.232 --> 00:04:14.984
Okay. and. uh...

94
00:04:15.943 --> 00:04:17.195
So...

95
00:04:17.278 --> 00:04:18.404
What else?

96
00:04:18.488 --> 00:04:19.864
A rubber giant.

97
00:04:22.116 --> 00:04:23.576
And a unicorn.

98
00:04:24.076 --> 00:04:25.328
That-That's everything.

99
00:04:25.912 --> 00:04:29.624
Okay. listen. my partner and I are gonna
be here for the next 30 minutes.

100
00:04:29.707 --> 00:04:34.170
Why don't you sit down. okay?
In case anything else comes to you.

101
00:04:34.253 --> 00:04:35.338
Okay. but you're gonna check it out?

102
00:04:35.421 --> 00:04:36.714
- Absolutely.
- Oh. absolutely.

103
00:04:36.798 --> 00:04:38.841
Thank you.
That's a huge relief.

104
00:04:38.925 --> 00:04:42.053
Unicorn... green circle...

105
00:04:42.136 --> 00:04:44.180
Green circle? Why does that sound fam...

106
00:04:45.765 --> 00:04:48.267
Bingo. I helped a buddy
renovate his dad's house.

107
00:04:48.351 --> 00:04:50.019
We used to drop stuff off here. Look.

108
00:04:50.102 --> 00:04:51.312
"Millrun Landfill."

109
00:04:51.395 --> 00:04:54.357
The logo of this place is a green circle.
Is that where the body is?

110
00:04:54.899 --> 00:04:56.234
Maybe.

111
00:04:59.195 --> 00:05:00.738
That is a rubber giant.

112
00:05:02.824 --> 00:05:06.244
There's no way Seymour expects us
to believe that story. Visions?

113
00:05:06.869 --> 00:05:09.789
He seems like such a nice kid.
Maybe he believes it?

114
00:05:09.872 --> 00:05:12.041
It doesn't matter.
There's no such thing as psychics.

115
00:05:12.124 --> 00:05:15.628
I don't know. Who am I to say?
I talked to my ghost mom in a toilet.

116
00:05:16.546 --> 00:05:19.215
And there's our unicorn.

117
00:05:21.384 --> 00:05:22.468
We must be getting close.

118
00:05:23.469 --> 00:05:24.470
Oh.

119
00:05:25.137 --> 00:05:28.224
- Ugh. Yeah. you smell that?
- Yeah. That's bad.

120
00:05:28.307 --> 00:05:30.393
Ugh. It's coming from that car.

121
00:05:30.476 --> 00:05:35.273
And seven flags on the bumper.
Oh. I can't...

122
00:05:46.033 --> 00:05:47.952
And a dead body in the trunk.

123
00:05:49.704 --> 00:05:52.164
Think Seymour had any psychic visions
about going to prison?

124
00:05:59.380 --> 00:06:01.966
This is just Appleyard trying
to make something out of nothing.

125
00:06:02.049 --> 00:06:03.843
I know.

126
00:06:04.343 --> 00:06:06.929
Good. You want to stop
wearing a groove in the floor?

127
00:06:08.472 --> 00:06:09.515
Got it.

128
00:06:11.392 --> 00:06:13.352
<i>And how did you know
he was in the house?</i>

129
00:06:13.895 --> 00:06:16.689
I heard a crash in the kitchen
and then I went to check.

130
00:06:16.772 --> 00:06:20.610
It was Dallas.
He was just trashing the place.

131
00:06:23.070 --> 00:06:24.280
And then he saw me.

132
00:06:28.075 --> 00:06:29.535
It's okay. Take your time.

133
00:06:31.621 --> 00:06:37.710
I could smell the alcohol on him.
and he was just so loud and angry.

134
00:06:39.253 --> 00:06:41.797
And then when
he started hitting me. I... I just...

135
00:06:43.966 --> 00:06:45.092
I knew that was it.

136
00:06:45.176 --> 00:06:46.177
What do you mean?

137
00:06:46.886 --> 00:06:48.429
That he was gonna kill me.

138
00:06:50.222 --> 00:06:54.101
I got free somehow. I locked myself
in the bedroom. And then I called Amanda.

139
00:06:54.685 --> 00:06:56.354
- You didn't call 911?
- I couldn't...

140
00:06:56.437 --> 00:06:57.521
I called it in.

141
00:06:57.605 --> 00:07:00.941
Appleyard knows that and we all know
what he's trying to do here.

142
00:07:01.025 --> 00:07:02.693
You're gonna be fine. Amanda.

143
00:07:02.777 --> 00:07:05.029
I'm not worried about me.

144
00:07:05.112 --> 00:07:06.572
<i>Tell me about the phone call.</i>

145
00:07:07.323 --> 00:07:10.743
<i>Amanda told me to get the gun.
And to defend myself.</i>

146
00:07:11.327 --> 00:07:14.914
And then I went out there.
andDallas came at me again.

147
00:07:17.792 --> 00:07:19.168
And I shot him.

148
00:07:19.251 --> 00:07:22.004
How long were you having an affair
with Amanda Wagner?

149
00:07:22.797 --> 00:07:23.923
What? No. we're-we're not...

150
00:07:24.006 --> 00:07:28.177
Your husband's anger that night. was
that because Amanda Wagner. your lover.

151
00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:30.513
<i>hauled him into the GBI to harass him?</i>

152
00:07:30.596 --> 00:07:33.474
He threw a rock through my window.
and she was just telling him to back off.

153
00:07:33.557 --> 00:07:34.767
Were you here for that questioning?

154
00:07:34.850 --> 00:07:36.644
- No. I...
- That's right. You couldn't have been.

155
00:07:36.727 --> 00:07:39.438
since Mr. Mavery had
a restraining order against you.

156
00:07:39.522 --> 00:07:40.648
Did you know about that?

157
00:07:41.482 --> 00:07:43.693
- No.
<i>- Dallas got that out of spite.</i>

158
00:07:43.776 --> 00:07:47.238
I had to get off of work and go down
to the courthouse and get that dropped.

159
00:07:47.321 --> 00:07:48.739
Now I'm... I'm here...

160
00:07:48.823 --> 00:07:52.993
Oh. I'm so sorry for the inconvenience.
It's protocol when you kill a man.

161
00:07:53.077 --> 00:07:56.497
Getting back to that. was your girlfriend
on the phone telling you how to do it

162
00:07:56.580 --> 00:07:58.624
or just how to stage
the crime scene afterwards?

163
00:07:58.708 --> 00:07:59.750
I need to stop this.

164
00:07:59.834 --> 00:08:00.876
Amanda. wait.

165
00:08:00.960 --> 00:08:02.545
- <i>Amanda didn't do anything.</i>
- Caroline.

166
00:08:02.628 --> 00:08:04.422
Dallas broke in.

167
00:08:04.505 --> 00:08:06.757
Are you sure he broke in?
There's no forced entry.

168
00:08:06.841 --> 00:08:09.677
It was an electric lock. I don't know.
Maybe he... he had a code or...

169
00:08:09.760 --> 00:08:12.847
Maybe. Sounds like you and Wagner
didn't get your story straight.

170
00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:14.974
Enough. Bill. Enough.

171
00:08:15.725 --> 00:08:18.060
We're done for now. Mrs. Mavery.
Thank you for your time.

172
00:08:18.728 --> 00:08:19.854
I'll walk you out. ma'am.

173
00:08:25.901 --> 00:08:29.155
"Just an initial interview"?
You knew where you were taking that.

174
00:08:29.238 --> 00:08:32.491
She should have had a lawyer present.
I'll have your badge. Bill.

175
00:08:32.575 --> 00:08:36.328
Deputy Director Wagner.
you are on administrative leave.

176
00:08:36.412 --> 00:08:39.957
That's straight from the director.
You will leave this building now.

177
00:08:50.009 --> 00:08:52.678
You want Amanda Wagner's job so badly.

178
00:08:53.804 --> 00:08:54.805
try earning it.

179
00:08:54.889 --> 00:08:58.225
I'm choosing to ignore
your outburst. Agent Trent.

180
00:08:58.309 --> 00:09:01.771
The deputy director of the GBI
must be unimpeachable.

181
00:09:01.854 --> 00:09:04.190
but as of now.
there are holes in this case.

182
00:09:04.273 --> 00:09:07.359
And you'd be able to see them.
if you didn't let your personal investment

183
00:09:07.443 --> 00:09:08.611
get in the way of your judgment.

184
00:09:08.694 --> 00:09:12.490
Now. you two are tasked with uncovering
exactly what happened last night.

185
00:09:12.573 --> 00:09:16.535
A woman shot her abusive husband
in self-defense. That is what happened.

186
00:09:16.619 --> 00:09:21.415
So. Mr. Mavery's been careful and precise.
stalking Mrs. Mavery for a year.

187
00:09:21.499 --> 00:09:24.168
Suddenly switches it up and attacks her?

188
00:09:24.877 --> 00:09:28.214
Find out why. Start by looking into him.

189
00:09:35.679 --> 00:09:37.098
- The door.
- I know.

190
00:09:37.848 --> 00:09:39.141
Her gun.

191
00:09:39.225 --> 00:09:40.226
I know.

192
00:09:40.851 --> 00:09:41.977
It's gonna be fine.

193
00:09:42.728 --> 00:09:43.729
Right.

194
00:09:46.273 --> 00:09:48.859
That was pretty gruesome. Seymour.

195
00:09:49.485 --> 00:09:51.821
The smell is still up in the nostrils.

196
00:09:51.904 --> 00:09:54.740
You did the right thing
by coming to us. Why?

197
00:09:56.117 --> 00:09:58.202
Because the guilt was eating you up.

198
00:09:58.285 --> 00:10:01.372
Write down what you did to that poor lady.
Get it all out.

199
00:10:01.956 --> 00:10:06.168
Come on. Tell me you're not doing
the pen and pad thing.

200
00:10:06.252 --> 00:10:08.003
Joanne. hi.

201
00:10:08.087 --> 00:10:10.965
Roger had a hearing. so I'm here.
Don't say or sign anything.

202
00:10:11.048 --> 00:10:13.050
- Well. I didn't kill her. I want to help.
- Shut up.

203
00:10:13.134 --> 00:10:14.802
Let him confess.
We all want the same thing here.

204
00:10:14.885 --> 00:10:16.595
Do we? I'm not so sure.

205
00:10:17.263 --> 00:10:19.515
- What are we talking about here?
- What are we talking about?

206
00:10:19.598 --> 00:10:20.599
Stop lawyering.

207
00:10:20.683 --> 00:10:22.893
How'd you know where
the body was if you didn't put her there?

208
00:10:22.977 --> 00:10:27.022
I told you. I get visions. okay?
They started when I was 12 or 13.

209
00:10:27.106 --> 00:10:29.650
Sometimes they're clearer.
sometimes they're more like puzzle pieces

210
00:10:29.733 --> 00:10:32.570
that don't really make sense
without the box for reference.

211
00:10:32.653 --> 00:10:33.904
Never bodies though.

212
00:10:33.988 --> 00:10:36.782
Seymour has psychic
abilities. It's how he makes his living.

213
00:10:36.866 --> 00:10:38.200
Sure. Scammer.

214
00:10:38.284 --> 00:10:39.910
What was your relationship
with Nikki Lane?

215
00:10:39.994 --> 00:10:43.539
We talked a few times
in the laundry room. She was nice.

216
00:10:43.622 --> 00:10:44.707
And pretty.

217
00:10:45.291 --> 00:10:46.375
You ever hit on her?

218
00:10:46.458 --> 00:10:48.752
I asked her out once. She said no.

219
00:10:48.836 --> 00:10:49.962
No harm in asking.

220
00:10:50.588 --> 00:10:54.925
Detailed calendar. T.A. schedule
to confirm Mr. Badgley's whereabouts.

221
00:10:55.009 --> 00:10:56.302
So prepared.

222
00:10:56.385 --> 00:10:59.513
I'm assuming you don't have any physical
evidence linking my client to this case.

223
00:11:00.639 --> 00:11:02.308
Is Mr. Badgley free to go now?

224
00:11:03.475 --> 00:11:05.769
Just don't leave town.
in case we have further questions.

225
00:11:05.853 --> 00:11:07.980
Great. Come on. Seymour.

226
00:11:12.276 --> 00:11:13.986
Joanne. wait. hold on.

227
00:11:14.069 --> 00:11:17.740
Hey. Hey. can I...
can I get a second without...

228
00:11:17.823 --> 00:11:19.992
I don't believe in secrets.
What is it. Detective?

229
00:11:21.577 --> 00:11:24.872
Okay. I'll start.
You said you would call me.

230
00:11:25.456 --> 00:11:27.750
I was meal prepping. and the kids...

231
00:11:27.833 --> 00:11:30.419
Meal prepping? Okay. sure.

232
00:11:30.502 --> 00:11:31.545
Um...

233
00:11:32.046 --> 00:11:34.882
I just... I thought we had a moment.
Maybe I was wrong.

234
00:11:36.300 --> 00:11:37.593
Take care.

235
00:11:38.427 --> 00:11:40.804
You're gonna see somebody soon. a woman.

236
00:11:40.888 --> 00:11:41.972
She's another body?

237
00:11:42.056 --> 00:11:44.099
No. no. no. she's alive. but she's cranky.

238
00:11:44.183 --> 00:11:47.937
Yeah. she's got some sort
of female troubles. you know. down there.

239
00:11:48.020 --> 00:11:49.021
Yeah.

240
00:11:49.104 --> 00:11:50.231
Get outta here.

241
00:11:50.314 --> 00:11:51.774
Also. watch out for the elephants.

242
00:11:51.857 --> 00:11:54.235
I certainly will because you told us to.

243
00:12:05.287 --> 00:12:07.081
Clearly. Seymour's been here before.

244
00:12:07.164 --> 00:12:09.500
She's Nikki's roommate.
he figured out we'd have to interview her.

245
00:12:09.583 --> 00:12:11.377
I didn't say anything.

246
00:12:13.212 --> 00:12:15.089
Oh. watch out for the elephants.

247
00:12:15.172 --> 00:12:17.383
Oh. it sounds so familiar.
Where have I heard that before?

248
00:12:17.466 --> 00:12:18.467
Shut it.

249
00:12:20.344 --> 00:12:22.638
- Hi.
- Oh. cookies.

250
00:12:23.597 --> 00:12:25.015
Did you bake those yourself. Ms. Matlin?

251
00:12:25.099 --> 00:12:26.100
Oh. she doesn't bake.

252
00:12:26.642 --> 00:12:27.893
She's right here.

253
00:12:28.686 --> 00:12:29.770
Hal likes to bake.

254
00:12:31.272 --> 00:12:33.816
So. uh. with regards to Nikki.

255
00:12:33.899 --> 00:12:36.860
is there anyone you can think of
who might have wanted to harm her?

256
00:12:37.653 --> 00:12:40.281
No. Nikki got along with everybody.

257
00:12:40.364 --> 00:12:42.866
Yeah. she was fun. So full of life.

258
00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:47.454
How about your neighbors.
specifically Seymour Badgley?

259
00:12:48.914 --> 00:12:50.165
I've never seen him before.

260
00:12:50.249 --> 00:12:52.668
So. the man in the photo.
he's never been in this apartment?

261
00:12:53.544 --> 00:12:56.505
No. Your shirt's riding up.

262
00:12:59.466 --> 00:13:00.884
Nature. right?

263
00:13:01.969 --> 00:13:04.305
Do you think
we should tell them about... You know?

264
00:13:06.056 --> 00:13:08.309
Hal. something you want to say?

265
00:13:08.392 --> 00:13:11.437
Nikki was fighting a lot lately
with her boyfriend. Lester.

266
00:13:12.855 --> 00:13:15.399
Do you have Lester's phone number. address?

267
00:13:15.482 --> 00:13:16.650
Yeah.

268
00:13:19.361 --> 00:13:21.280
- Do you want a cookie?
- Oh. yes. please.

269
00:13:21.363 --> 00:13:22.489
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

270
00:13:27.036 --> 00:13:30.622
Dallas withdrew cash from the ATM inside
two hours before he died.

271
00:13:32.333 --> 00:13:33.917
Establishes his timeline.

272
00:13:34.418 --> 00:13:36.795
How do we prove
a bad man has bad intentions?

273
00:13:40.049 --> 00:13:44.136
<i>♪ I-N-D-E-P-E-N-D-E-N-T
Do you know what that mean. mane? ♪</i>

274
00:13:44.219 --> 00:13:49.016
<i>♪ I-N-D-E-P-E-N-D-E-N-T
Do you know what that mean? ♪</i>

275
00:13:49.099 --> 00:13:51.977
<i>♪ She got her own house
She got her own car ♪</i>

276
00:13:52.061 --> 00:13:55.105
<i>♪ Two jobs. work hard. you a bad broad ♪</i>

277
00:13:55.189 --> 00:13:57.858
<i>♪ If you ain't on. sit down
If you ain't on. sit down ♪</i>

278
00:13:57.941 --> 00:14:00.360
<i>♪ If you ain't on. sit down
If you ain't on. sit down ♪</i>

279
00:14:01.153 --> 00:14:06.283
<i>♪ I-N-D-E-P-E-N-D-E-N-T
Do you know what that mean? ♪</i>

280
00:14:06.366 --> 00:14:09.078
<i>♪ Baby Phat. just relax
Front your own flat screen ♪</i>

281
00:14:09.161 --> 00:14:12.039
<i>♪ Back rub. cook. clean
And don't make her make a scene ♪</i>

282
00:14:12.122 --> 00:14:14.291
<i>♪ Got her stunna shades on.
Lookin' like something ♪</i>

283
00:14:14.374 --> 00:14:15.667
Pardon me. ma'am.

284
00:14:15.751 --> 00:14:18.212
Um. I believe this. uh. came from...

285
00:14:18.921 --> 00:14:21.048
Ah. yes. your-your left ear.

286
00:14:22.549 --> 00:14:24.718
Important to stay symmetrical. Um...

287
00:14:26.678 --> 00:14:28.305
Hope you have a prosperous evening.

288
00:14:31.225 --> 00:14:34.019
<i>♪ Flip flop slippers just
To show off the pedicure ♪</i>

289
00:14:36.605 --> 00:14:40.067
I like this. Are you two really cops.
or is this some kind of kink?

290
00:14:40.150 --> 00:14:43.821
I am an armed agent of the GBI.
Stop touching me.

291
00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:45.697
My bad.

292
00:14:45.781 --> 00:14:48.867
Bouncer said that Dallas Mavery
was your regular.

293
00:14:48.951 --> 00:14:50.702
What kind of mood was he in last night?

294
00:14:50.786 --> 00:14:56.125
The generous kind. I made good money too.
He was real happy with me.

295
00:14:56.208 --> 00:14:57.835
Then he started going in about his ex.

296
00:14:57.918 --> 00:14:59.920
These guys think
we're marriage counselors.

297
00:15:00.003 --> 00:15:01.630
But this was way worse.

298
00:15:01.713 --> 00:15:03.298
What exactly did he say about her?

299
00:15:03.382 --> 00:15:06.343
Calling her all kinds of bitches.
"I hate her. I'm gonna kill her."

300
00:15:06.426 --> 00:15:07.636
Did something set him off?

301
00:15:07.719 --> 00:15:09.346
That's the thing. Nothing happened.

302
00:15:09.429 --> 00:15:11.974
I tried to calm him down.
get him to eat something. sober up.

303
00:15:12.057 --> 00:15:14.726
He wouldn't listen to me. Then he left.

304
00:15:16.979 --> 00:15:18.689
He didn't actually hurt her. did he?

305
00:15:18.772 --> 00:15:21.567
Dallas Mavery was killed
after leaving the club last night.

306
00:15:22.568 --> 00:15:24.486
Oh. damn.

307
00:15:25.821 --> 00:15:28.115
Pearl. you got a private dance request.

308
00:15:29.616 --> 00:15:30.617
Make us that money.

309
00:15:32.119 --> 00:15:34.872
Did I just hear you right? Dallas is dead?

310
00:15:37.457 --> 00:15:38.667
Were you and Dallas friends?

311
00:15:39.376 --> 00:15:43.172
Hell no. It's strictly transactional
in here. Fool owed me money.

312
00:15:43.255 --> 00:15:45.132
Why did Dallas owe you money?

313
00:15:45.215 --> 00:15:47.009
He tried to run out on his bill.

314
00:15:47.092 --> 00:15:50.721
He was up in here last night.
acting like he King of the South.

315
00:15:50.804 --> 00:15:53.724
Ordering a bottle of Dom.
top-shelf shots. chicken wings.

316
00:15:53.807 --> 00:15:55.559
I did hear the wings are excellent.

317
00:15:55.642 --> 00:15:57.102
My grandmama recipe.

318
00:15:57.186 --> 00:15:58.979
You said Dallas tried to run out?

319
00:15:59.062 --> 00:16:02.941
His card declined.
But he swore he was good for it.

320
00:16:03.025 --> 00:16:04.693
Said he got some big payout coming.

321
00:16:04.776 --> 00:16:06.278
Did he say from where?

322
00:16:06.361 --> 00:16:08.363
His old lady
just inherited two million dollars.

323
00:16:08.947 --> 00:16:11.617
Look. just let me know if there's
some type of form I need to fill out

324
00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:12.701
so I can get my cash.

325
00:16:12.784 --> 00:16:13.785
Damn.

326
00:16:15.329 --> 00:16:18.332
Two million dollars. Dallas had motive.

327
00:16:19.208 --> 00:16:21.919
Yeah. but so did Casey.

328
00:16:25.214 --> 00:16:27.466
How much trouble
are you in because of me?

329
00:16:27.549 --> 00:16:29.468
No. none-none of this is your fault.

330
00:16:31.011 --> 00:16:33.722
But I do wish you'd told me
about the inheritance money.

331
00:16:34.389 --> 00:16:36.892
When would I?
We just started seeing each other.

332
00:16:36.975 --> 00:16:39.436
My dad passed away.

333
00:16:39.519 --> 00:16:42.272
He had leukemia.
but he did pretty well for himself.

334
00:16:43.065 --> 00:16:45.984
Everything was caught up
in probate for over a year.

335
00:16:46.068 --> 00:16:48.695
Honestly. it was the last thing
on my mind.

336
00:16:48.779 --> 00:16:51.031
Of course.

337
00:16:51.114 --> 00:16:54.493
I guess the estate lawyer didn't know
that Dallas and I had separated.

338
00:16:54.576 --> 00:16:58.664
She emailed both of us saying
the funds had been wired to my bank.

339
00:16:58.747 --> 00:17:00.499
When was that email sent?

340
00:17:01.124 --> 00:17:02.834
Day before yesterday.

341
00:17:02.918 --> 00:17:04.670
That must have been what triggered him.

342
00:17:06.046 --> 00:17:11.385
Next thing I know. he's in my home
demanding his half of the money.

343
00:17:14.721 --> 00:17:15.889
Then he started...

344
00:17:20.185 --> 00:17:23.772
Hey. Hey. hey. you're here.
You're here. you're okay.

345
00:17:23.855 --> 00:17:28.527
Yeah. even in death. this man
is ruining the good parts of my life.

346
00:17:28.610 --> 00:17:34.366
Oh. no. he's not touching this.
We're good. Yeah?

347
00:17:36.201 --> 00:17:37.244
Yeah.

348
00:17:46.753 --> 00:17:49.715
Appleyard wants to meet in an hour.

349
00:17:50.799 --> 00:17:53.594
Listen. Casey.
I know his playbook.

350
00:17:53.677 --> 00:17:55.053
If there's anything else he can use.

351
00:17:55.137 --> 00:17:57.764
I need you to tell me
so I'm not blindsided.

352
00:17:59.766 --> 00:18:00.892
You have everything.

353
00:18:05.230 --> 00:18:07.065
Tell me you asked Joanne out. right?

354
00:18:07.149 --> 00:18:09.151
Do I pry into your relationship
with Dr. Seth?

355
00:18:09.234 --> 00:18:10.611
Do you ever not?

356
00:18:10.694 --> 00:18:12.404
Let's just talk to the boyfriend.

357
00:18:12.487 --> 00:18:14.114
Pete. what do you got?

358
00:18:14.197 --> 00:18:18.410
Autopsy results for Nikki Lane.
Cause of death was strychnine.

359
00:18:18.493 --> 00:18:21.204
- She ingested it. And it gets worse.
- Oof.

360
00:18:21.288 --> 00:18:22.748
Worse than someone poisoning her?

361
00:18:22.831 --> 00:18:25.792
Ms. Lane was two months pregnant.

362
00:18:26.418 --> 00:18:27.419
Geez.

363
00:18:28.211 --> 00:18:30.172
Thanks. Pete.

364
00:18:31.923 --> 00:18:33.550
- You okay?
- Yeah.

365
00:18:35.886 --> 00:18:37.554
No. let's get this asshole.

366
00:18:39.056 --> 00:18:40.307
Lester Clump.

367
00:18:42.726 --> 00:18:45.395
Uh. yes. I am Lester Clump.

368
00:18:45.479 --> 00:18:48.440
This is Barry. my brother.
I... mean attorney.

369
00:18:48.523 --> 00:18:49.941
You a real lawyer. Barry?

370
00:18:50.025 --> 00:18:52.736
I mean. online degrees are valid.

371
00:18:52.819 --> 00:18:55.030
Good enough to walk you
through your confession.

372
00:18:55.113 --> 00:18:57.908
Why did you kill your girlfriend. Nikki?

373
00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:00.160
Barry can't help you.

374
00:19:00.744 --> 00:19:02.287
Was it because she was pregnant?

375
00:19:02.371 --> 00:19:03.372
Pregnant?

376
00:19:03.455 --> 00:19:05.499
- What my client means...
- Shut up. Barry.

377
00:19:07.584 --> 00:19:09.544
I think you knew about the baby.

378
00:19:09.628 --> 00:19:12.172
- I didn't know...
- Did Nikki tell you? No? Somebody else?

379
00:19:13.215 --> 00:19:15.926
Did you find that positive test
in the trash?

380
00:19:16.009 --> 00:19:17.761
That can be a lot. It can be a shocker.

381
00:19:17.844 --> 00:19:20.472
Is that why you killed
your pregnant girlfriend?

382
00:19:20.555 --> 00:19:22.307
Wait. how pregnant was she?

383
00:19:22.391 --> 00:19:23.600
Two months.

384
00:19:23.684 --> 00:19:25.477
We hadn't had sex in six months.

385
00:19:25.560 --> 00:19:29.856
I went to Maine to take care of our nana.
I was there for four months.

386
00:19:30.941 --> 00:19:33.110
When I got back.
Nikki didn't seem interested anymore.

387
00:19:33.193 --> 00:19:36.780
She was spending all her time
with Reba and her fiancé.

388
00:19:36.863 --> 00:19:40.742
Okay. we are still gonna need a DNA sample
to rule out paternity.

389
00:19:42.285 --> 00:19:44.621
Help yourself out here. man.

390
00:19:44.705 --> 00:19:48.208
If the baby's not yours. that means
we get to look into a different suspect.

391
00:19:51.169 --> 00:19:53.463
Fine. we're done for now.

392
00:20:05.684 --> 00:20:08.478
Just take this to the lab.
see if it's a match.

393
00:20:08.562 --> 00:20:10.689
- So dumb.
- Yeah.

394
00:20:10.772 --> 00:20:12.441
- I don't think he's our guy.
- No.

395
00:20:12.524 --> 00:20:14.735
Is it okay to hate a stupid person?

396
00:20:14.818 --> 00:20:15.944
I think so.

397
00:20:19.614 --> 00:20:23.702
Hope you don't mind if my FOP Rep
sits in on our little impromptu meeting.

398
00:20:23.785 --> 00:20:28.165
Interesting news regarding Casey Mavery's
inheritance. Did you know about that?

399
00:20:28.248 --> 00:20:29.499
No. I didn't. Bill.

400
00:20:29.583 --> 00:20:32.794
These are text messages
between you and Casey Mavery.

401
00:20:32.878 --> 00:20:35.714
more accurately from you to Mrs. Mavery.

402
00:20:35.797 --> 00:20:37.466
Inspector. I hope you obtained a warrant...

403
00:20:37.549 --> 00:20:39.301
...for the Deputy Director's text messages.

404
00:20:39.384 --> 00:20:42.637
"Amanda: Make sure
to keep the gun nearby."

405
00:20:42.721 --> 00:20:47.267
"Amanda: You're protected
as long as you're inside your home."

406
00:20:47.350 --> 00:20:49.853
"Amanda: It's called Stand Your Ground."

407
00:20:49.936 --> 00:20:54.191
"Amanda: I can still smell
your perfume on me."

408
00:20:54.274 --> 00:20:57.903
"Amanda: Remember. aim for center mass."

409
00:20:58.779 --> 00:21:01.198
You're only reading my half
of the conversation. Bill.

410
00:21:01.281 --> 00:21:02.908
Casey was asking me questions.

411
00:21:02.991 --> 00:21:04.159
All right. let me see those.

412
00:21:09.748 --> 00:21:11.625
This does seem rather one-sided.

413
00:21:12.125 --> 00:21:13.960
Casey uses voice messaging.

414
00:21:14.044 --> 00:21:16.129
I'm at work. so I generally type.

415
00:21:16.213 --> 00:21:18.298
And I didn't save hers.

416
00:21:18.381 --> 00:21:22.511
The warrant was handled
by the GBI director personally.

417
00:21:22.594 --> 00:21:25.138
Edie? Why?

418
00:21:25.806 --> 00:21:29.434
Because we need to assess whether you.
Deputy Director Wagner.

419
00:21:29.518 --> 00:21:31.061
are an accessory to murder.

420
00:21:34.773 --> 00:21:38.360
No DNA match. Lester is not the father.

421
00:21:39.194 --> 00:21:40.278
Still could've killed her.

422
00:21:40.362 --> 00:21:43.824
Yeah. possibly.
You know what I've been thinking about?

423
00:21:43.907 --> 00:21:45.367
You want an online legal degree?

424
00:21:45.450 --> 00:21:48.537
Yeah. And that Joanne didn't come here
to help out a colleague.

425
00:21:48.620 --> 00:21:52.249
She came to see you. Smart. Funny.

426
00:21:52.332 --> 00:21:55.752
What if Nikki was having "cookies"
with Reba's fiancé?

427
00:21:55.836 --> 00:21:56.920
Just say sex.

428
00:21:57.462 --> 00:22:01.883
Yeah. Uh. what's his name?
Hal. Passive Hal.

429
00:22:01.967 --> 00:22:03.176
Yeah. let's go talk to him.

430
00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:05.136
You noticed she also smells great?

431
00:22:05.220 --> 00:22:06.847
- Stop.
- Who smells great?

432
00:22:06.930 --> 00:22:08.682
Don't answer that. We don't have time.

433
00:22:08.765 --> 00:22:10.100
Seymour. tell them what you told me.

434
00:22:10.183 --> 00:22:11.852
This feels familiar.

435
00:22:11.935 --> 00:22:13.353
Yeah. isn't this how we met?

436
00:22:13.436 --> 00:22:14.604
Oh. so you do remember?

437
00:22:14.688 --> 00:22:16.690
Of course I remember.
You made quite an impression.

438
00:22:16.773 --> 00:22:18.567
But meal prepping took precedent.

439
00:22:18.650 --> 00:22:20.318
You're out of my league. There.

440
00:22:20.402 --> 00:22:24.072
Really glad you guys are talking.
Let's hear what Seymour has to say.

441
00:22:24.155 --> 00:22:25.907
I saw another body.

442
00:22:25.991 --> 00:22:29.244
Yeah. well. you better have an address
this time. No more scavenger hunts.

443
00:22:32.205 --> 00:22:36.710
Sandwich. Pickle. Red flashing light.

444
00:22:36.793 --> 00:22:40.255
Delivery truck getting towed. 12th Street.

445
00:22:40.338 --> 00:22:41.840
12th?

446
00:22:41.923 --> 00:22:43.633
Hal lives on 12th.

447
00:22:46.344 --> 00:22:52.350
I get wanting to help Casey.
It's just the optics.

448
00:22:52.434 --> 00:22:54.102
Bill wants my job.

449
00:22:54.185 --> 00:22:56.146
He thinks I just gave him
the key to my office.

450
00:22:56.229 --> 00:22:57.647
Why is there glitter in your hair?

451
00:22:57.731 --> 00:23:02.068
Oh. it's-it's from Pearl. the dancer from
Magic City that Will and I interviewed.

452
00:23:02.152 --> 00:23:05.822
You know. Dallas had to be
one miserable person to be raging mad

453
00:23:05.906 --> 00:23:11.119
amidst all of that... and all of those...
and the glitter.

454
00:23:11.202 --> 00:23:13.455
- Stripper glitter never comes off.
- Really?

455
00:23:13.538 --> 00:23:16.374
Mm-hmm. Just so you know.

456
00:23:17.208 --> 00:23:23.214
Look at us. Aunt Mandy.
We both fell hard and fast for somebody.

457
00:23:24.007 --> 00:23:27.135
You still haven't read any of those
letters from Malcolm yet. have you?

458
00:23:28.136 --> 00:23:31.556
You know Caroline
tells me everything. Why not?

459
00:23:33.391 --> 00:23:35.352
I can imagine what's in them.

460
00:23:35.435 --> 00:23:39.689
Apologies. sweet words.
Malcolm was good with words.

461
00:23:39.773 --> 00:23:41.191
Hmm.

462
00:23:41.274 --> 00:23:45.403
If I do read them.
then I would have to admit

463
00:23:45.487 --> 00:23:48.448
that I let myself love somebody
that I shouldn't have.

464
00:23:50.325 --> 00:23:52.202
I don't know where you're going
with this. but-but...

465
00:23:52.285 --> 00:23:54.913
- Aunt Mandy...
- No. no. no. It's not the same.

466
00:23:54.996 --> 00:23:57.666
I didn't wanna believe it either
with Malcolm. Not in the beginning.

467
00:23:57.749 --> 00:24:01.086
It was good. It was exciting.
And you miss things.

468
00:24:01.169 --> 00:24:03.254
And that was you. not me.

469
00:24:03.338 --> 00:24:06.549
Is there even a possibility
that Casey used your position...

470
00:24:06.633 --> 00:24:08.510
- Don't go there. Faith.
- Dallas is dead.

471
00:24:08.593 --> 00:24:11.096
and you are the only one being punished.
The only one.

472
00:24:11.179 --> 00:24:14.849
So-So is that what you think of
me? That I'm some gullible old lady who...

473
00:24:14.933 --> 00:24:16.643
No. no. I do not think that.
I am just saying...

474
00:24:16.726 --> 00:24:20.313
Here's the truth. Casey begged for help.
but the police told her

475
00:24:20.397 --> 00:24:23.441
that their hands were tied
unless Dallas actually killed her.

476
00:24:23.525 --> 00:24:27.445
They said that out of their mouths
to a victim of domestic assault.

477
00:24:28.822 --> 00:24:31.950
Aunt Mandy. listen. Mandy.

478
00:24:32.993 --> 00:24:36.579
They gave her a restraining order.
which did nothing to prevent him

479
00:24:36.663 --> 00:24:38.581
from sitting in his truck
and watching her.

480
00:24:39.332 --> 00:24:44.170
Casey would be dead right now
if she hadn't killed him first.

481
00:24:44.254 --> 00:24:45.588
I'll see myself out.

482
00:24:45.672 --> 00:24:47.507
Don't go. I'm sorry.

483
00:25:06.860 --> 00:25:09.362
Hey. Will.
Dallas's truck was never confiscated.

484
00:25:10.030 --> 00:25:12.282
I'm gonna have it towed
to the impound lot. Meet me there.

485
00:25:17.078 --> 00:25:19.748
Anything new on your uncle?
I saw you check the phone.

486
00:25:21.958 --> 00:25:22.959
Nope.

487
00:25:23.543 --> 00:25:25.253
You wanna talk about it?

488
00:25:26.337 --> 00:25:27.672
Not really.

489
00:25:34.721 --> 00:25:35.722
I haven't slept.

490
00:25:36.598 --> 00:25:39.893
Antonio could be dead or worse.
Nobody has any answers.

491
00:25:39.976 --> 00:25:42.979
And I'm digging through a wife-beater's
truck instead of finding my uncle.

492
00:25:44.314 --> 00:25:46.066
Maybe I did need to talk about it.

493
00:25:46.816 --> 00:25:47.984
Thank you.

494
00:25:53.364 --> 00:25:54.407
You okay?

495
00:25:54.491 --> 00:25:56.659
Not really. This job is...

496
00:25:56.743 --> 00:25:57.827
Yeah.

497
00:25:57.911 --> 00:26:00.246
- It's all split-second decisions.
- And paperwork.

498
00:26:00.330 --> 00:26:02.332
One wrong choice
and your career's on the line.

499
00:26:02.415 --> 00:26:04.834
and then everybody's judging you harshly.

500
00:26:05.585 --> 00:26:06.669
Amanda mad at you?

501
00:26:07.504 --> 00:26:08.588
Furious.

502
00:26:09.297 --> 00:26:10.465
Well. then let's keep looking.

503
00:26:11.841 --> 00:26:12.884
Yeah.

504
00:26:12.967 --> 00:26:14.219
Oh. I think I got something.

505
00:26:14.302 --> 00:26:15.678
Come on. come on.

506
00:26:15.762 --> 00:26:17.514
Got it.

507
00:26:18.014 --> 00:26:19.015
Oh. hello.

508
00:26:19.599 --> 00:26:21.267
All right. Let's get it to Rocky.

509
00:26:22.102 --> 00:26:24.479
- Maybe we can see what Dallas was up to.
- Yeah.

510
00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:32.195
Seymour was right
about Hal living on 12th Street.

511
00:26:32.278 --> 00:26:33.530
Lucky guess.

512
00:26:34.405 --> 00:26:35.406
What about that?

513
00:26:35.490 --> 00:26:38.743
Red flashing light.
delivery truck getting towed.

514
00:26:39.911 --> 00:26:41.079
Lucky guess.

515
00:26:44.290 --> 00:26:46.209
Sandwich and a pickle.

516
00:26:46.918 --> 00:26:48.586
Seymour's been here. That's all.

517
00:26:48.670 --> 00:26:49.671
You hear that?

518
00:27:01.558 --> 00:27:02.934
Strychnine poisoning.

519
00:27:03.017 --> 00:27:05.979
His health. height and weight
delayed the poison's speed.

520
00:27:06.062 --> 00:27:09.190
It caused his muscles to spasm.
probably explains the bruising.

521
00:27:09.691 --> 00:27:12.152
He stumbled off his balcony.
The awning caught him.

522
00:27:13.027 --> 00:27:14.529
He's lucky you guys found him.

523
00:27:15.738 --> 00:27:17.365
Same poisoning as Nikki.

524
00:27:17.448 --> 00:27:21.077
Yeah. Nikki. who's roommates
with Hal's fiancée.

525
00:27:21.161 --> 00:27:24.455
I bet Reba slipped a secret ingredient
into Hal's cookies.

526
00:27:24.539 --> 00:27:26.416
Are you doing
the cookie/sex metaphor again?

527
00:27:26.499 --> 00:27:29.752
This time I mean she poisoned him
because Hal got Nikki pregnant.

528
00:27:29.836 --> 00:27:31.129
Got it. Yep.

529
00:27:34.048 --> 00:27:36.676
Did you find anything
on Dallas's phone we could use?

530
00:27:36.759 --> 00:27:39.012
Uh. incoming call at 9:00 p.m.

531
00:27:39.095 --> 00:27:40.597
He would've still been in the strip club.

532
00:27:40.680 --> 00:27:43.349
Pearl didn't mention him getting
a phone call. You trace the number?

533
00:27:43.433 --> 00:27:44.767
It was a burner. Sorry.

534
00:27:44.851 --> 00:27:47.103
Well. someone called and talked to Dallas.

535
00:27:47.186 --> 00:27:49.230
I'm guessing they said something
that triggered him.

536
00:27:49.314 --> 00:27:51.774
So there is something else.

537
00:27:51.858 --> 00:27:54.277
A HomeCam app on the phone
was linked to this address.

538
00:27:54.360 --> 00:27:56.112
- What? Seriously.
- You should've led with that.

539
00:27:56.195 --> 00:27:58.156
Well. I was trying to build suspense.

540
00:27:58.239 --> 00:27:59.532
Why?

541
00:27:59.616 --> 00:28:00.867
This is Casey's house.

542
00:28:00.950 --> 00:28:02.994
Dallas planted a camera to spy on her.

543
00:28:03.077 --> 00:28:05.038
- Anything else?
- I swear to God. Rocky.

544
00:28:05.121 --> 00:28:06.414
Okay. Okay.

545
00:28:06.497 --> 00:28:09.208
Uh. there's a video of the night he died.

546
00:28:09.834 --> 00:28:11.628
Give me that.

547
00:29:16.818 --> 00:29:17.986
I think we're done.

548
00:29:22.031 --> 00:29:23.950
Reba Matlin. APD.

549
00:29:27.787 --> 00:29:28.871
So many elephants.

550
00:29:28.955 --> 00:29:30.289
- Check the bedroom.
- Okay.

551
00:29:35.837 --> 00:29:36.838
Clear!

552
00:29:50.018 --> 00:29:51.728
These are fertility meds she's on.

553
00:29:56.649 --> 00:29:57.692
She's pregnant?

554
00:29:58.609 --> 00:30:00.987
She was. It's dated a year and a half ago.

555
00:30:01.070 --> 00:30:04.365
So that's what Seymour meant when
he said she was having female trouble.

556
00:30:06.951 --> 00:30:07.952
What the hell?

557
00:30:09.454 --> 00:30:11.497
Reba!

558
00:30:11.581 --> 00:30:12.790
Reba. stop! APD!

559
00:30:16.169 --> 00:30:17.712
Reba. stop!

560
00:30:18.880 --> 00:30:20.298
APD! Stop!

561
00:30:22.800 --> 00:30:23.801
Reba!

562
00:30:35.980 --> 00:30:36.981
Reba.

563
00:30:41.778 --> 00:30:43.946
Reba. it's Detective Angie Polaski.

564
00:30:44.447 --> 00:30:46.449
I need you to step back here by me.

565
00:30:50.203 --> 00:30:51.788
Reba. we found Hal.

566
00:30:52.747 --> 00:30:53.831
He's alive.

567
00:30:54.665 --> 00:30:56.876
Why don't you come down here
and talk to me about it?

568
00:30:59.295 --> 00:31:00.546
What about my baby?

569
00:31:01.172 --> 00:31:05.635
Yeah. Why don't we find somewhere safe.
and you can show me your baby?

570
00:31:17.647 --> 00:31:19.315
Nikki was drinking.

571
00:31:21.025 --> 00:31:22.276
I smelled it on her.

572
00:31:25.238 --> 00:31:26.989
I told her to stop. but she just...

573
00:31:28.032 --> 00:31:31.702
But what? Reba. what happened?

574
00:31:31.786 --> 00:31:34.372
I had to make her stop.

575
00:31:35.206 --> 00:31:36.290
I had to.

576
00:31:36.791 --> 00:31:39.001
Nikki didn't deserve to be a mom.

577
00:31:42.964 --> 00:31:45.299
We do. Right?

578
00:31:46.717 --> 00:31:47.802
You...

579
00:31:47.885 --> 00:31:49.470
You really wanted to be a mom.

580
00:31:50.930 --> 00:31:52.098
I'm a good mom.

581
00:31:54.851 --> 00:31:57.645
Right. baby? Mommy's here.

582
00:32:10.992 --> 00:32:14.996
Okay. I need... We need you to sign this.

583
00:32:15.496 --> 00:32:16.831
Oh. is that what we need?

584
00:32:17.623 --> 00:32:20.209
I can sign
if that's what we're talking about.

585
00:32:20.293 --> 00:32:23.504
Yes. I looked it over.
You can sign them for Detective Ormewood.

586
00:32:24.380 --> 00:32:26.382
I prefer it when you call me Michael.

587
00:32:26.966 --> 00:32:28.050
Take care. Detective.

588
00:32:31.304 --> 00:32:33.556
I know you don't believe me
about my visions.

589
00:32:34.056 --> 00:32:36.309
Even though they did help solve your case.

590
00:32:37.185 --> 00:32:38.269
What's your point?

591
00:32:38.352 --> 00:32:40.021
I saw something else.

592
00:32:40.813 --> 00:32:42.940
It's good though. It's about you. You two.

593
00:32:43.024 --> 00:32:44.942
- Who? Me and Joanne?
- Yep.

594
00:32:46.277 --> 00:32:49.405
Yeah. Okay. Hold on a second.

595
00:32:55.453 --> 00:32:56.454
Go ahead.

596
00:32:57.038 --> 00:32:59.790
You... Joanne.

597
00:33:00.833 --> 00:33:04.295
Looks like a date.
A park with a little bridge.

598
00:33:04.795 --> 00:33:07.340
A bridge? Enota Park?

599
00:33:07.423 --> 00:33:09.342
I guess. Tomorrow at 3:00.

600
00:33:09.425 --> 00:33:10.760
Okay. I'll try to catch her.

601
00:33:10.843 --> 00:33:12.720
Hold on. I can tell you
what foods to pack.

602
00:33:12.803 --> 00:33:14.055
I know how to plan a picnic.

603
00:33:14.138 --> 00:33:16.224
All right. suit yourself.
But bring a blanket.

604
00:33:16.307 --> 00:33:17.558
Of course. What am I. stupid?

605
00:33:17.642 --> 00:33:19.936
I don't know. Visions don't show IQ.

606
00:33:21.062 --> 00:33:24.106
The weather's gonna be perfect.
Joanne will love it. Trust me.

607
00:33:24.690 --> 00:33:27.151
Okay. Thanks.

608
00:33:41.249 --> 00:33:43.000
It is over. right?

609
00:33:45.795 --> 00:33:46.879
Yes.

610
00:33:52.843 --> 00:33:54.262
And what about you?

611
00:33:55.596 --> 00:33:56.764
All clear.

612
00:33:58.307 --> 00:33:59.308
It's over.

613
00:34:06.524 --> 00:34:09.527
I'm gonna take a quick shower.
You wanna join?

614
00:34:10.569 --> 00:34:14.365
Sure. Just got to check in
with Faith first.

615
00:34:14.865 --> 00:34:15.866
- Okay.
- Okay.

616
00:34:29.463 --> 00:34:31.090
Hey. you have a charger?

617
00:34:54.780 --> 00:34:55.865
Stripper glitter?

618
00:35:04.290 --> 00:35:08.377
I'm gonna ask you one more time.
Where can I find Pearl?

619
00:35:08.461 --> 00:35:10.046
I wish I can help.

620
00:35:10.129 --> 00:35:12.715
Her locker was cleared
when I got here for my shift today.

621
00:35:17.803 --> 00:35:19.055
Where'd Pearl go?

622
00:35:19.722 --> 00:35:22.642
She kept talking about going to Vegas
to be a showgirl.

623
00:35:22.725 --> 00:35:24.977
I didn't realize she meant. like. today.

624
00:35:25.519 --> 00:35:27.521
How long she's been making these plans?

625
00:35:28.314 --> 00:35:29.315
A month.

626
00:35:30.358 --> 00:35:35.112
She got herself a sugar mama.
Gave her 150K to get out of some mess.

627
00:35:35.196 --> 00:35:38.699
I wish I could find me a sugar mama.
You looking?

628
00:35:55.257 --> 00:35:56.592
You're vegan. aren't you?

629
00:35:58.094 --> 00:36:01.138
I am. But this tomato.
I mean. is this heirloom?

630
00:36:01.222 --> 00:36:04.725
It's great. It's like a...
It's like a handheld salad.

631
00:36:05.643 --> 00:36:08.270
How about some wine?
I got a great bottle. It's...

632
00:36:08.354 --> 00:36:10.731
At least I hope it's great.
It was expensive.

633
00:36:10.815 --> 00:36:12.400
Yeah. maybe later.

634
00:36:13.734 --> 00:36:15.277
I get migraines.

635
00:36:16.195 --> 00:36:18.114
I guess I don't know
how to plan a picnic after all.

636
00:36:18.197 --> 00:36:21.158
You wouldn't happen to have a falafel
in that basket. would you?

637
00:36:21.242 --> 00:36:22.827
Did I screw this up?

638
00:36:23.411 --> 00:36:24.662
Absolutely not.

639
00:36:25.246 --> 00:36:27.957
I'm just glad
you finally called.

640
00:36:28.040 --> 00:36:30.543
I was starting to think
maybe that I imagined our...

641
00:36:30.626 --> 00:36:31.627
Connection?

642
00:36:32.253 --> 00:36:35.297
No. that was very real. Is very real.

643
00:36:36.215 --> 00:36:37.216
Good.

644
00:36:37.717 --> 00:36:40.302
Oof. Are you cold? It's gotten colder.
right? It's not just me?

645
00:36:40.386 --> 00:36:41.762
No. I'm freezing.

646
00:36:41.846 --> 00:36:44.640
I should have never listened to...
You know what? It doesn't matter.

647
00:36:44.724 --> 00:36:46.350
- You wanna go somewhere warm?
- Please.

648
00:36:46.434 --> 00:36:48.185
Okay. All right.

649
00:36:49.520 --> 00:36:51.397
Take this. Sorry. it's cold.

650
00:36:57.862 --> 00:37:01.615
Hey. keep going. okay? Don't wait for me.
Shield yourself. Joanne.

651
00:37:04.326 --> 00:37:05.828
- Can I get two. please?
- Two falafel?

652
00:37:05.911 --> 00:37:07.538
Yeah. Two falafels. thanks.

653
00:37:08.038 --> 00:37:09.623
- Here you go.
- Here.

654
00:37:10.332 --> 00:37:11.751
- Keep it.
- Thank you.

655
00:37:13.878 --> 00:37:15.671
What are the odds?

656
00:37:17.923 --> 00:37:19.091
That-That's like...

657
00:37:19.967 --> 00:37:20.968
Oh. boy.

658
00:37:21.510 --> 00:37:25.347
That's my most favorite song. Like ever.

659
00:37:25.431 --> 00:37:26.474
No way.

660
00:37:26.557 --> 00:37:27.600
Way.

661
00:37:28.809 --> 00:37:30.728
I really like you. Michael.

662
00:37:31.812 --> 00:37:34.899
No more of this. like.
out-of-my-league talk. okay?

663
00:37:34.982 --> 00:37:37.485
No. leagues don't exist. Banished.

664
00:37:39.612 --> 00:37:40.613
I like you too.

665
00:37:42.448 --> 00:37:49.079
<i>♪ I don't wanna close my eyes
I don't wanna fall asleep ♪</i>

666
00:37:49.163 --> 00:37:51.624
<i>♪ 'Cause I'd miss you. babe ♪</i>

667
00:37:51.707 --> 00:37:54.585
<i>♪ I don't wanna miss a thing ♪</i>

668
00:37:54.668 --> 00:37:57.546
<i>♪ Even when I dream of you ♪</i>

669
00:37:58.756 --> 00:38:03.761
<i>♪ The sweetest dream will never do
I'd still miss you. baby ♪</i>

670
00:38:03.844 --> 00:38:06.806
<i>♪ Don't wanna miss a thing ♪</i>

671
00:38:14.939 --> 00:38:21.195
<i>♪ I don't wanna close my eyes
I don't wanna fall asleep ♪</i>

672
00:38:21.278 --> 00:38:22.279
Caroline.

673
00:38:25.825 --> 00:38:28.452
Hey. Can you take this
to the shredder for me?

674
00:38:29.995 --> 00:38:31.872
You sure you want me to shred all of them?

675
00:38:31.956 --> 00:38:33.290
I am. Thanks.

676
00:38:33.374 --> 00:38:39.797
<i>♪ I'd still miss you. baby
Don't wanna miss a thing ♪</i>

677
00:38:39.880 --> 00:38:41.590
<i>♪ I don't wanna miss...</i>

678
00:38:42.758 --> 00:38:45.261
<i>...a thing ♪</i>

679
00:38:46.303 --> 00:38:48.472
You are the FBI.

680
00:38:48.556 --> 00:38:51.600
And you're telling me
between your agency and Interpol.

681
00:38:51.684 --> 00:38:53.644
you have no sightings of Adelaide Trevens?

682
00:38:55.980 --> 00:39:00.067
How about the. uh. the-the kid I met.
The Commander?

683
00:39:00.150 --> 00:39:01.735
Any ID on him yet?

684
00:39:05.030 --> 00:39:09.076
Okay. No. no. No. it has not rung yet.

685
00:39:11.161 --> 00:39:14.164
That's my hope as well. Thank you. yep.

686
00:39:30.848 --> 00:39:32.808
Don't worry. boss.
Stuff's ready to go.

687
00:39:32.892 --> 00:39:34.643
That's the last of the books.
Thank...

688
00:39:36.937 --> 00:39:38.105
That was fast.

689
00:39:39.815 --> 00:39:41.650
Needed a new start.

690
00:39:42.610 --> 00:39:44.528
Atlanta's got a lot of memories.

691
00:39:44.612 --> 00:39:48.198
You and Pearl headed to Vegas.
or are you done using her too?

692
00:39:48.282 --> 00:39:49.491
Yeah. Yeah. I got it.

693
00:39:50.326 --> 00:39:52.119
Uh. you guys wanna take a quick break?

694
00:39:52.202 --> 00:39:53.871
Sure. We're almost loaded anyway.

695
00:40:00.336 --> 00:40:02.254
I didn't use you. Amanda.

696
00:40:02.338 --> 00:40:04.089
You knew I was GBI.

697
00:40:04.757 --> 00:40:06.675
You knew I'd understand your pain.

698
00:40:07.676 --> 00:40:11.221
So you invited me here to see
Dallas's violence firsthand.

699
00:40:11.305 --> 00:40:14.516
But it was Pearl who threw the rock
through the window.

700
00:40:14.600 --> 00:40:16.894
Yeah. tell her to ease up
on the glitter next time.

701
00:40:16.977 --> 00:40:19.855
- Let me explain.
- No. no. I got it.

702
00:40:21.023 --> 00:40:25.903
You paid Pearl to manipulate Dallas
and then lied to my agents about it.

703
00:40:26.946 --> 00:40:29.865
Oh. he didn't just up and leave
the club that night.

704
00:40:31.075 --> 00:40:32.826
You called him from a burner phone.

705
00:40:34.119 --> 00:40:37.456
What did you say to make him so upset?

706
00:40:37.539 --> 00:40:40.125
You think that man ever needed an excuse?

707
00:40:41.919 --> 00:40:44.338
He was gonna kill me eventually.

708
00:40:44.421 --> 00:40:46.382
No one was gonna stop that. not even you.

709
00:40:46.465 --> 00:40:48.092
Oh. you're trying to justify murder now.

710
00:40:48.175 --> 00:40:51.011
I used what little resources I had
to save my own life.

711
00:40:54.181 --> 00:40:57.935
What we have. it's a good thing.

712
00:40:59.853 --> 00:41:01.605
Nothing that has happened undoes that.

713
00:41:02.231 --> 00:41:03.899
It's all undone.

714
00:41:05.401 --> 00:41:08.904
You lied. You didn't even tell me
you were leaving town.

715
00:41:08.988 --> 00:41:11.031
So what if I did? What were you gonna do?

716
00:41:11.115 --> 00:41:13.117
I wasn't gonna make you carry this too.

717
00:41:13.200 --> 00:41:14.660
Oh. please.

718
00:41:15.369 --> 00:41:17.997
You're leaving now because you care
about what happens to me?

719
00:41:18.080 --> 00:41:19.581
I do. I really...

720
00:41:19.665 --> 00:41:20.749
Don't!

721
00:41:21.291 --> 00:41:23.168
Don't.

722
00:41:23.794 --> 00:41:26.588
Unlike you. I have unlimited resources.

723
00:41:26.672 --> 00:41:27.965
I can come after you.

724
00:41:28.590 --> 00:41:30.426
The case is closed. Amanda.

725
00:41:31.343 --> 00:41:32.469
If you reopen it.

726
00:41:32.553 --> 00:41:35.806
you're gonna have to admit
that it happened under your watch.

727
00:41:37.099 --> 00:41:38.934
Think about your reputation.

728
00:41:39.768 --> 00:41:40.936
Your career.

729
00:41:42.021 --> 00:41:47.818
So you think my only options are
to throw away everything I worked for...

730
00:41:49.820 --> 00:41:51.572
or to let you get away with this?

731
00:41:53.449 --> 00:41:55.200
I wish we had another option.

732
00:41:56.785 --> 00:41:57.953
Do we?

733
00:42:00.122 --> 00:42:01.123
No.
